<Author>7Bluebells
<Content>Clean, spacious and excellent location. Would stay again. Just off the busy La Rambla the Hotel Peninsular location is fantastic: being within a short walking distance of most of Barcelona's attractions. The hotel is basic but very clean.Most if not all of the staff are friendly, and will appreciate it if you make an effort to talk to them in Spanish. We stayed during festival week in Barcelona and the hotel was full. Bear in mind before you book that this hotel is very popular with students, so it can get a bit noisy at night. We didn't get back till late most nights so we didn't really find it a problem and the staff at the hotel asked people to keep it down if and when they did come in late. We only went to breakfast once during our 9-day stay, as we preferred to go to a cafe instead. Breakfast is nothing to get excited about and consists of 2 rolls and a cake. Don't bother looking for meals on La Rambla, they're pricey and bland, instead we went to the gothic quarter most nights. Just around the corner from the hotel (the first turning off the road the hotel is on as you walk to La Rambla) there's a good restaurant/ cocktail bar and a organic vegetarian restaurant where we went on a few occasions and wasn't disappointed. I would stay here again as its fantastic value for money and as I mentioned before the location is excellent. 
