<Content>Well situated, good budget hotel! We arrived and found the hotel with no problems, just a couple of minutes walk from the vibrant Las Ramblas (get off at Liceu Metro stop). We were pleasantly surprised after reading some reviews on this website which were sometimes negative. The Staff were friendly and helpful. The hotel has some great features, especially the atrium in the centre. You could see some history here, unlike many modern hotels. The room was basic but was ok for us as we are young travellers and were hardly ever in. You don't need luxury when the whole of the city is on your doorstep. I would ask for a room with a balcony or window if you don't mind a bit of noise at night (ours didn't have a window so we couldn't tell what the weather was like!).If you are travelling on a shoestring, we would recommend that you go further into town for food and drink, as La Ramblas is very pricey. Across the road a few blocks down is Placa Reial (sp?) which has some great bars with nice food and drink and brilliant atmosphere without the huge pricetag. There is also a supermarket on La Ramblas where you can buy cheap food to take to a picnic when you are saving the pennies. Get the tube to Parc De La Citudella (Arc de Triomp stop).Enjoy and keep an eye on your bag/camera as pickpockets are apparently rife in that area. The tarrif at the hotel is 拢50 for a double room so bear in mind if booking with travel agent as we paid nearly 拢70. 
