<Content>Save your pennies - stay at the Peninsular! We stayed at the Peninsular for four nights in May 2003. Impressive reception area and the indoor courtyard with the balconies made us gasp. Slightly different gasp when we opened the door of our room. Well, it was once a nun's cell! We'd been warned it was basic and it's definitely better than camping. It was tatty but clean and we will certainly visit Barcelona again and will stay at the Peninsular too - only next time I will buy a big bunch of flowers in the Ramblas to brighten the room up and bring coloured scarves to drape over the lights. Romantic it is not. The staff were great - very amenable and good humoured. The first thing the receptionist did was warn us about the pickpocketing scams and I recommend visiting **** before you go. We would not have wanted to walk much further down the street (away from the Ramblas) at night. The clientele ranged from backpackers to smart middle aged and older. Very noisy at night so we bought earplugs from the chemist a few doors away then no problem. Check out the frijoles and the creme catalunya at the restaurant Romesco in the Carer Saint Pau right by the Peninsular. The hotel and this restaurant are so cheap you will have plenty of spare cash for the very tasteful tourist momentoes and a splurge at the Camper shoe shop. They say you get what you pay for but I believe that you get more than you pay for at the Peninsular. 
