<Content>Still itching! We just returned from a four nights stay in Hotel Peninsular, which was recommended to us by a colleague. To tell the truth, we won't follow a recommendation of him again! Yes, the architecture of the building (courtyard) is quite nice and interesting. Yes, the staff is friendly and helpful. Yes. it is centrally located. However, seeing the first room, we decided to have a look into another one. It was not really an improvement. The rooms are really, really basic (you are lucky if you got a window). There was no curtain in the shower, so imagine how the bath looked like after two people went through it. There was a daily room maid, but obviously the cloth has not been changed for a long time. Sheets seemed to be O.K. - watching our skin today, you might get some sort of animals as a souvenir. This hotel is not that cheap as it is basic. 
